"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510022","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-04-13","<p>The Ministry of Defence has signed several hundred Treaties, Agreements, Memoranda of Understandings and Letters of Intent with foreign governments since 2011. These agreements are a key part of our defence engagement work and a list of the countries that are party to these agreements will be deposited in the Library of the House shortly.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2016-04-13T14:40:44.727Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510022/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510022/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510022/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-04-11","Military Alliances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with which countries the UK has signed a defence (a) treaty, (b) formal agreement, (c) Memorandum of Understanding and (d) Letter of Intent in each year since 2011.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","33410"
