"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510083","Department of Health","false","2016-04-14","<p>The Department does not hold this information centrally.</p><p>However, as far as NHS England is aware, in the overwhelming majority of cases, leaders are not being paid over and above the remuneration they receive for their existing roles. Many Sustainability and Transformation Plans are supported by local programme teams which are funded by the constituent local organisations.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-04-14T13:03:10.553Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510083/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510083/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510083/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-04-11","NHS: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the total cost to the public purse has been of establishing the Sustainability and Transformation Plan Footprints Leadership Teams.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","33344"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510084","Department of Health","false","2016-04-14","<p>Being a Sustainability and Transformation Plan (STP) leader is a voluntary, non-statutory role. As far as NHS England is aware, in the overwhelming majority of cases, leaders are not being paid over and above the remuneration they receive for their existing roles.</p><p> </p><p>The role of the STP leaders is to support the development of STPs which are expected to be submitted in July 2016.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-04-14T13:23:47.807Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510084/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510084/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510084/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-04-11","NHS: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether the posts of NHS Sustainability and Transformation Plan Footprints Leaders are remunerated; and how long appointments to those posts are for.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","33345"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510085","Department of Health","false","2016-04-14","<p>Sustainability and Transformation Plan areas have been determined by local health and care services coming together in ways that make sense for their local areas, in order to transform the way that health and care is planned and delivered for their populations.</p><p>Following local discussions about who is best placed to play the role of footprint leaders, together with discussions with national bodies, 41 of the 44 planning areas have identified and agreed leaders.</p><p>They are mostly a mix of trust chief executive officers, clinical commissioning group leaders and local government executives.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman","33347 ; 33348","2016-04-14T12:59:14.767Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510085/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510085/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510085/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-04-11","NHS: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether appointments to the posts of NHS Sustainability and Transformation Plan Footprint Leaders were subject to open selection.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","33346"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510086","Department of Health","false","2016-04-14","<p>Sustainability and Transformation Plan areas have been determined by local health and care services coming together in ways that make sense for their local areas, in order to transform the way that health and care is planned and delivered for their populations.</p><p>Following local discussions about who is best placed to play the role of footprint leaders, together with discussions with national bodies, 41 of the 44 planning areas have identified and agreed leaders.</p><p>They are mostly a mix of trust chief executive officers, clinical commissioning group leaders and local government executives.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman","33346 ; 33348","2016-04-14T12:59:14.827Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510086/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510086/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510086/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-04-11","NHS: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the recruitment process was for the appointment of NHS Sustainability and Transformation Plan Footprint Leaders; and what criteria were used to appoint to those posts.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","33347"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510087","Department of Health","false","2016-04-14","<p>Sustainability and Transformation Plan areas have been determined by local health and care services coming together in ways that make sense for their local areas, in order to transform the way that health and care is planned and delivered for their populations.</p><p>Following local discussions about who is best placed to play the role of footprint leaders, together with discussions with national bodies, 41 of the 44 planning areas have identified and agreed leaders.</p><p>They are mostly a mix of trust chief executive officers, clinical commissioning group leaders and local government executives.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman","33346 ; 33347","2016-04-14T12:59:14.897Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510087/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510087/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510087/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-04-11","NHS: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, who was responsible for appointing the NHS Sustainability and Transformation Plan Footprint Leaders.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","33348"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510088","Department of Health","false","2016-04-14","<p>The Department has begun its DH2020 programme which, amongst other things, aims to reduce the size of the Department by about one third over the course of this parliament. As a result the Department is anticipating moving from around 2,000 roles to around 1,300-1,400 over this time period.</p><p>To deliver the reductions, the Department will offer Voluntary Exits and a three month redeployment period for displaced staff, prior to moving to Voluntary Redundancy and Compulsory Redundancy, if necessary. Taking this into account, numbers of redundancies are expected to be lower than the headline numbers given above.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-04-14T08:13:58.85Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510088/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510088/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/510088/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-04-11","Department of Health: Redundancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, (a) how many and (b) what proportion of the officials of his Department he expects to be made redundant by the end of 2016.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","33367"
